  'lincoln-county': { slug: 'lincoln-county', countyName: 'Lincoln County', countySeat: 'Chandler', population: 34972, courthouseAddress: '811 Manvel Ave, Chandler, OK 74834', heroLead: 'Named by popular vote in 1891 to honor President Abraham Lincoln, Lincoln County sits at the geographic heart of Oklahoma and was once the top cotton-producing county in the state. Today, this east-central Oklahoma county blends its agricultural heritage with oil and gas production, Sac and Fox Nation tribal enterprises, and Route 66 tourism along the historic Mother Road. Whether you need process served at the Lincoln County Courthouse in Chandler, the Sac and Fox tribal court in Stroud, or anywhere across the county\'s 966 square miles, Just Legal Solutions delivers prompt, professional service throughout Lincoln County — call (539) 367-6832 or visit /contact.' },
